# Bug-to-Monster Workflow

**CRITICAL**: Every bug found in this codebase MUST strengthen the Monster Army.

## The Workflow

When ANY bug is discovered (by user, testing, production, code review, etc.):

1. **Record** - Document the bug with `npm run monsters:learn`
2. **Analyze** - Identify which monster SHOULD have caught it
3. **Enhance** - Add detection code to that monster
4. **Verify** - Run the monster to confirm it now catches this bug type

## Quick Reference

```bash
# Record a new bug interactively
npm run monsters:learn

# View learning statistics
npm run monsters:learn:stats

# See pending learnings
cat tests/qa/monsters/pending-learnings.md
```

## Which Monster to Update

| Bug Category | Primary Monster | File |
|---|---|---|
| UI crashes | browser-qa | `browser-monster/browser-qa-monster.ts` |
| Visual issues | product-quality | `browser-monster/product-quality-monster.ts` |
| API errors | api-monster | `api-monster/api-monster.ts` |
| Validation bugs | contract-monster | `contract-monster/contract-monster.ts` |
| Security issues | guardian-monster | `guardian-monster/guardian-monster.ts` |
| Game logic bugs | invariant-monster | `invariant-monster/poker-invariants.ts` |
| Tournament bugs | tournament-flow | `flows/tournament-flow-monster.ts` |

## When Fixing a Bug

After you fix a bug, ALWAYS:

1. Ask: "How could our monsters have caught this earlier?"
2. Add detection code to the appropriate monster
3. Run `npm run monsters:all:fast` to verify

## Example: Adding Detection

If you fix a bug where a form submits with empty fields:

```typescript
// In browser-qa-monster.ts, add:
const emptySubmit = await page.evaluate(`
  (() => {
    const forms = document.querySelectorAll('form');
    for (const form of forms) {
      const requiredEmpty = form.querySelectorAll('[required]:invalid');
      if (requiredEmpty.length > 0) {
        return { hasIssue: true, form: form.id || 'unknown' };
      }
    }
    return { hasIssue: false };
  })()
`);
if (emptySubmit.hasIssue) {
  this.addFinding("BUG", "high", "Form allows empty submission", 
    `Form ${emptySubmit.form} has invalid required fields`, url);
}
```

## The Goal

**We should NEVER see the same type of bug twice.**

Each bug makes the Monster Army smarter, building an ever-growing safety net that catches issues before they reach production.
